	     Monrovia - Former football star George Weah won Liberia's presidential run-off with a projected 61.5% of the vote, the country's election commission said on Thursday. Weah handily beat Vice President Joseph Boakai, who secured 38.5%, the National Election Commission (NEC) said, with 98.1% of votes counted. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  